# LeadHub MVP — V0 Foundation Walkthrough

## What Was Built

Complete V0 Foundation for a multi-tenant B2B Lead/CRM web application.

### Project Structure
```
talepgetir-leadhub-exp/
├── .env                    ← Supabase keys (you fill in)
├── .env.example
├── package.json            ← npm workspaces (server + client)
├── PLANNING.md
├── server/                 ← Node.js API (Express + TypeScript)
│   └── src/
│       ├── index.ts        ← Express app entry
│       ├── lib/supabase.ts ← Admin + user Supabase clients
│       ├── middleware/
│       │   ├── auth.ts     ← JWT validation + role check
│       │   └── errorHandler.ts
│       └── routes/
│           ├── auth.ts     ← Login, refresh, /me
│           └── companies.ts ← Full CRUD + pagination
├── client/                 ← React (Vite + Mantine + i18n)
│   └── src/
│       ├── App.tsx         ← Router + providers
│       ├── i18n.ts         ← TR/EN language setup
│       ├── lib/api.ts      ← Axios with token refresh
│       ├── contexts/AuthContext.tsx
│       ├── components/
│       │   ├── Layout.tsx  ← AppShell header + user menu
│       │   └── CompanyForm.tsx ← Create/Edit modal
│       ├── pages/
│       │   ├── LoginPage.tsx ← Gradient login page
│       │   └── LeadsPage.tsx ← Data table + pagination
│       └── locales/
│           ├── tr.json     ← Turkish translations
│           └── en.json     ← English translations
└── supabase/
    └── migrations/
        └── 001_foundation.sql ← Tables, RLS, indexes, triggers
```

### Backend API Endpoints
| Method | Path | Auth | Description |
|--------|------|:----:|-------------|
| `POST` | `/api/auth/login` | ❌ | Email/password login |
| `POST` | `/api/auth/refresh` | ❌ | Refresh token |
| `GET` | `/api/auth/me` | ✅ | Current user + tenant info |
| `GET` | `/api/companies` | ✅ | List with pagination |
| `GET` | `/api/companies/:id` | ✅ | Get single company |
| `POST` | `/api/companies` | ✅ ops/admin | Create company |
| `PUT` | `/api/companies/:id` | ✅ ops/admin | Update company |
| `DELETE` | `/api/companies/:id` | ✅ superadmin | Delete company |

### DB Tables (with RLS)
`tenants`, `memberships`, `companies`, `activities` (DB only, UI in V4)

